XML_CASESUMMARY.SUMMARY:
This two vehicle crash occurred mid-afternoon during daylight hours in the westbound lanes of a five lane dry, asphalt roadway. There are two westbound and two eastbound lanes that are separated by a continuous left turn lane. The roadway is straight with a posted speed limit of 56 KPH (35 MPH). the sky was clear. Traffic flow was moderate at the time of the crash.
Vehicle one(V-1), a 2001 Nissan Sentra sedan driven by a 39 year-old male with one passenger was stopped in eastbound turn lane. Vehicle two (V-2), a 2005 Toyota Corolla sedan driven by a 24 year-old female was traveling westbound in the #2 lane. V-1 entered the left turn lane and stopped for about 2-3 seconds behind three other non-contact vehicles also stopped in the left turn lane for the red light at the intersection ahead. The vehicle then began to make a left turn across the path of V-2. The right front side of V-1 was struck by the front of V-2. The impact caused V-1 to rotate counterclockwise and travel across the westbound lanes coming to rest partially in the #1 and #2 westbound lanes facing in a westerly direction. V-2 was traveling through the intersection and struck V-1 just to the west of the intersection. The impact caused V-2 to rotate clockwise and enter the #1 westbound lane coming to rest in that lane facing in a northwesterly direction. The vehicles came to rest within 2 meters of each other. The driver of V 1 stated that he had just left the pizza place and stopped in the left turn lane intending to turn into the convenience store to grab a soda. He advised that he was stopped behind three other vehicles in the left turn lane for about 2-3 seconds before continuing to turn left. The driver said that he did not see V-2 approaching until he already begun to make the left turn and was already in the vehicles lane. The vehicle was towed due to damage. The driver of V 2 stated that she saw V 1 turning left in front of her, she hit her brakes (no lock up). V 2 was towed from the scene.
The critical pre crash event for V1 was coded this vehicle traveling-turning left at intersection. The critical reason was coded driver related factor-inadequate surveillance. (The driver either did not look or looked but did not see V-2 approaching from the right.
An associated factor for this crash was the vehicles stopped in the left turn lane that created a sight line restriction for both vehicles involved in this crash.
The critical pre crash event for V2 was coded other vehicle encroachment-from opposite direction over the left lane line. The critical reason was not coded to this vehicle.
An associated factor for this vehicle was the vehicles stopped in the left turn lane creating a sight line restriction for the driver of V-2.
